ts=2026-06-12T16:27:17.564Z action=deleted original_ts=2026-06-12T16:19:13.283Z type=preference scope=code-style content="When the user provides code snippets to include in summaries, do NOT copy them verbatim. Always refactor to match established conventions: `this->` for member access, `data` (not `info`) for node members, `nullptr` (not NULL), C++11 style (constructors, destructors, templates, `auto`), 2-space indentation in code blocks." reason="Updated to: When the user provides code snippets to include in summaries, do NOT copy them verbatim. Always refactor to match established conventions: `this->` for member access, `data` (not `info`) for node members, `nullptr` (not NULL), classic constructor style (body initialization, NOT member initializer list), 2-space indentation in code blocks."
